      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TARPS (4) went forward and proved too strong when first-up scoring by 2.5 lengths over 1000m here on the turf. Proven second-up and races well on the poly. Will likely control the race and take beating. KING OF MINTO (2) was only beaten 1.8L at Doomben and then didn't get into it after an awkward start on the Gold Coast turf. Won his only go here over the distance and rates to threaten. SPIRIT OF BRODIE (3) showed good speed and fought on for third over 1000m at Toowoomba, first up. Has more to give and has to be considered. ADALIE (6) rated similarly at Toowoomba in the same contest but was plain in Open grade at Dalby following. Has her first try here and can go better. COUNT NICHOLAS (5) has the rail and is knocking on the door. In the mix.",
